{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Generate a Shopify homepage section with:
    
    • 1 hero section at top with full-width parallax background.
    • Single H1 in hero: “Premium Wall Art & Professional UV Printing Services”.
    • Subheading: “Shop premium wall art collections or book UV printing services with same-day production.”
    • Two CTA buttons:
      - “Shop By Category” → links to /#wall-art-categories section ID
      - “Book Services” → links to /#printing-services section ID
    
    Below hero, create two main silos with clean SEO heading hierarchy:
    
    1) H2: “Paintings & Posters by Category” (id="wall-art-categories")
       Under this H2, add a 4-card grid. Each card has:
       - H3 title linking to collection:
         • Canvas Paintings  → /collections/canvas-paintings
         • Metal Posters → /collections/metal-posters
         • Acrylic Posters → /collections/acrylic-posters
         • UV Printed Frames → /collections/uv-printed-frames
       - Short 15–20 word description
       - Small parallax-style image area
       - Button: “Explore Collection”
    
    2) H2: “Printing Services by Category” (id="printing-services")
       Under this H2, add a 4-card grid. Each card has:
       - H3 title linking to collection:
         • UV Flatbed Printing → /collections/uv-flatbed-printing
         • Eco-Solvent Printing → /collections/eco-solvent-printing
         • Latex Printing → /collections/latex-printing
         • Signage Printing → /collections/signage-printing
       - Short 15–20 word description
       - Parallax-style image area
       - Button: “View Service”
    
    Requirements:
    • Only one H1 on the page (in hero).
    • Use H2 only for the two silos, H3 only for the category/service cards.
    • Add a single <script type="application/ld+json"> block at the end with WebPage schema and two ItemList entries (one for wall art categories, one for printing services), using the same URLs as above.
    • Use simple inline CSS for parallax effects and responsive grid layout (desktop and mobile).
    
{% enddoc %}
